sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K260000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a fosmid based on pCC2Fos from EPICENTRE Biotechnologies (http://www.epibio.com/item.asp?ID=385). It contains 38 kb from the human MECP2 genomic locus, with a spectinomycin resistance (SpecR) cassette in the first intron of MECP2.
This fosmid is used to accept by recombineering the HincII fragment from BBa_K260016 (inside backbone BBa_K260010). This reaction also transfers the blasticidin resistance gene (BsdR) to generate the new backbone BBa_K260001 (pCC2FosMB), then containing the same BBa_K260016 part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kaj Bernhardt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
EPICENTRE Biotechnologies (http://www.epibio.com/item.asp?ID=385)
human MECP2 genomic sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Intron 1 of MECP2 previously contained a BsdR cassette. This had to be changed to SpecR by recombineering to generate the present fosmid.
